Code Review For Sprint 5
Review workflow:
Sprint 5 reviews were coordinated through Discord. Team members posted pull requests, requested reviewers, discussed feedback, and confirmed fixes in the server so implementation, review, and testing context stayed visible to the group.

Pull Requests:
added CSV file for room 2 #28 request by Isaac Gonzales reviewed by Liuyc05
Strengths:
Successfully converted room 2 into a CSV file and added it to Content > rooms. This improves the project’s room data organization and makes future room editing and loading more manageable.
Technical Concerns / Suggestions:
The CSV conversion work is useful, but more validation may be needed to ensure all room data is correctly preserved after conversion. It is also suggested to keep the room formatting and naming conventions consistent for future room files.

updated room 4 blocks / converted to csv #29 request by Isaac Gonzales reviewed by Liuyc05
Strengths:
Successfully updated the room 4 blocks and converted the room data into CSV format. This helps standardize the room structure and supports easier maintenance of level data.
Technical Concerns / Suggestions:
It would be helpful to verify that the new block placements exactly match the intended room design after conversion. Future improvements could include documenting the CSV structure more clearly for teammates working on level editing.

level 5 blocks replaced #30 request by Isaac Gonzales reviewed by Liuyc05
Strengths:
Successfully replaced the level 5 blocks and added the CSV file for the fifth level. This contributes to the custom level layout workflow and keeps the room data pipeline more consistent.
Technical Concerns / Suggestions:
The implementation should be further tested to confirm that all replaced blocks behave correctly in gameplay. It may also be helpful to review whether the room layout remains balanced and visually consistent after the replacement.

Finish the implement and place the spring, moveBlock and crushBlock #31 request by Liuyc05 reviewed by Luu5uu
Strengths:
Successfully completed the implementation and placement of Spring, MoveBlock, and CrushBlock. This adds important interactive gameplay elements and improves the completeness of the level design.
Technical Concerns / Suggestions:
Although the block placement is working well, additional testing may still be needed to ensure the interactions between these objects remain stable in different gameplay situations. It may also help to further polish object spacing and placement for smoother player experience.

Madeline rewind #32 request by Luu5uu reviewed by KeenRSH
Strengths:
Successfully added the Madeline rewind feature and contributed to dash recharge behavior. This introduces a creative gameplay mechanic and expands the player movement system in a meaningful way.
Technical Concerns / Suggestions:
Since rewind directly affects player state and movement logic, more testing may be needed to ensure it works consistently with collisions, room transitions, and other mechanics. Dash refill behavior was later refined so wall grab/contact alone does not restore dash, keeping the feature more intuitive and fair in gameplay.

Feather movement #37 request by hfritz34 reviewed by Luu5uu
Strengths:
Successfully implemented a comprehensive flight system via the FlyFeather item and StarFly state, fully integrated with the rewind system. Introduced polished environmental and movement particles, fixed wall jump mechanics, and refactored the collision system to support lift momentum.
Technical Concerns / Suggestions:
Given the significant volume of changes (15 commits, ~1,700 lines) to core physics and collision logic, extensive regression testing is recommended to ensure stability across all rooms. Continued monitoring of particle system performance is advised for long-term playability.
